'''Morten Veland''' (born [[December 4]], [[1977]]) was one of the founding members of the [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[gothic metal]] band [[Tristania (band)|Tristania]]. 

Whilst in Tristania, he was the main lyricist, songwriter and guitarist<ref>[http://www.sirenia.no/index.htm sirenia homepage]</ref> as well as being responsible for the [[death grunt|growling vocals]], until he left Tristania after the first two full length albums due to social and musical differences.<ref>[http://www.gothmetal.net/article/articleview/302/1/33/ gothmetal.net, tristania]</ref>

After that he formed his own band [[Sirenia (band)|Sirenia]], composing the same genre of music, in which he contributes nearly all of the instruments as well as the growling vocals. The rest of the band are mostly used on live performances only.

== Discography ==
====with Tristania====
* ''[[Tristania (EP)|Tristania]]'' (EP, 1997)
* ''[[Widow's Weeds]]'' (1998)
* ''[[Beyond the Veil (album)|Beyond the Veil]]'' (1999)
* ''[[Angina (EP)|Angina]]'' (1999)

====with Sirenia====
* ''[[At Sixes and Sevens]]'' (2002)
* ''[[An Elixir For Existence]]'' (2004)
* ''[[Sirenian Shores]]'' (EP, 2004)
* ''[[My Mind's Eye]]'' (Single, 2007)
* ''[[Nine Destinies and a Downfall]]'' (2007)

